                "20 cm from the neutron source."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " EJ-200 scintillator with diameter of 1.5cm and",
                "height of 4.5 cm was used as active sample - a",
                "scatter detector. Detector was used as time of flight",
                "stop detector with threshold of a constant fraction",
                "discriminator fixed at 60 keV electron energy. The",
                "swinger magnet was rotated around scatter detector",
                "to provide different scattering angles."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Three liquid-scintillation neutron detectors",
                " (NE213, D = 12.7 cm, H = 5.08 cm, PMT RCA 4522) were",
                "placed at a flight path of 4.108m from the",
                "scatter-detector."
              ]
            }
          ],
